Uncertainty Principle
A localized wavepacket contains a spread of momenta. Higher momenta travel faster, causing the packet to spread.
sigma(t) = sigma_0 * sqrt(1 + (hbar*t/2m*sigma_0^2)^2)
Split-Operator Method
FFT transforms to momentum space where kinetic energy is diagonal. Exact unitary evolution!
psi(t+dt) = F^-1[e^(-i*hbar*k^2*dt/2m) * F[psi]]
